cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper is about learning to control the movements of a robot arm, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian optimization and PID controllers suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of PAMs, which are a type of actuator, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper includes experimental results and tracking performance, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) for analyzing the robot's movements.
